public @interface DevKitGenerated

The DevKitGenerated annotation is used to mark the class that has been generated by the DevKit. The annotation is recorded in the class file by the compile and is retained by the VM at runtime. The DevKit product version and build number elements are required. The date element is optional and is used to indicate the date the source was generated and must follow the ISO 8601 standard. The comment element is optional and is a place holder for any comments that may want to be included in the annotation.
